es the features of waterborne disease surveillance, including disease reporting, outbreak detection, tracking of pathogens in drinking water sources, and effects of meteorological factors on waterborne diseases. The challenges discussed suggest the need for integrated surveillance systems that utilize novel data sources and state-of-the-art epidemiological methods.","publicationCount":0,"publicationCountByYear":[],"citationCnt":0,"citationCountByYear":[],"rank":21741.0,"entityType":0},"dataVersion":"2019-01-11-prod"}